article.description: David Jean-Baptiste scored a career-high 25 points as Chattanooga beat South Alabama 90-72 on Friday night.
article.headline: Jean-Baptiste leads Chattanooga past South Alabama 90-72
article.linkText: Jean-Baptiste leads Chattanooga past South Alabama 90-72
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- David Jean-Baptiste scored a career-high 25 points as Chattanooga beat South Alabama 90-72 on Friday night. Jean-Baptiste sank 10 of his 14 shots, including 5 of 6 on 3-pointers. Matt Ryan added 20 points for the Mocs (3-1). Ramon Vila had 17 points, while Rod Johnson added five assists. Andre Fox had 24 points for the Jaguars (2-2), but he made just 2 of 7 from distance as they shot 24% (5 of 21). Chad Lott added 18 points and seven rebounds. Josh Ayeni scored 12. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
